args: Ain't she done smokin' the meat yet?
I'm afraid you'll have to hold on\na little bit longer, Ranzal.
I can't wait no longer! The soup's ready,\nyeah? It's just GOTTA be ready!
Praise Ilia, but you are a child sometimes.\nCleo told us it needs to simmer for quite\na while before serving, remember?
Well, hell. Guess I'll just stare\nat the fire and go hungry instead.
Still, who'da thunk the boss would suggest\na camping party? I'm impressed!
It is certainly giving everyone a\nmuch-needed chance to unwind.
Good, clean air and good, clean food! \nHeckuva combo! Good on ya, boss!
I appreciate the kind words, but I'm not\nthe one who put this together.
Just didn't expect ya to be the drivin'\nforce behind a wild shindig is all.
Even I have a desire to cut loose \nevery once in a while.
Additionally, this party will serve\nanother important function.
Well, you see... *sniff*\nEr, is something burning?
The smoked food is on fire! Put it out!
Forget the soup—we have to get\nthis fire under control!
Phew! We managed to put it out.
Er, sorry about that. I shoulda been\nwatching a little closer.
I must apologize as well. I knocked over\nthe soup in my panic to put the fire out...
It's fine, Elly. No one was hurt,\nand that's all that matters.
Except the food's all burned to cinders\nand now we got nothin' to eat!
We threw every last ingredient we had\ninto dinner. *sniff* Think I'm gonna cry...
Don't worry. I'll not let you go hungry.
As I was starting to say earlier, this party\nis going to serve an important function.
Did you notice anything special about\nthe menu for tonight's event?
Just that I wanted to eat all of it—\nbut I guess that ain't unusual.
Oh I know! All of the ingredients are things\nthat can be found in the mountains, woods,\nand lakes in this area.
Indeed. Nothing on tonight's menu was\nmade from what we bought at the market.
Everything was naturally found in the wild.\nTherefore...
We can quickly replace everything that\nwas lost by foraging near the shore!
*chomp* So good! Three cheers for Cleo!
Hard to believe you just whipped this up!
I thought the herbs we gathered were \nmere weeds, and yet they've cooked up\nrather pleasantly.
You really can make anything taste good.
It's a good thing I've had the chance\nto practice my outdoor cooking.
Why WERE ya doin' that anyway?
We're going to keep getting sent out\non long assignments, and won't always\nbe able to carry adequate supplies.
So I've been practicing foraging\nand preparing food in the wild.
Tonight's party was also about having all\nof you try your hand at some of the recipes\nI've thought up.
After all, I won't be able to accompany\nyou on every trip.
Okay, but why bring us out to the lake?\nWe could have learned just as well\nback at the Halidom.
But then you'd be missing out on the most\nimportant spice for this cuisine...
It certainly has been a lovely meal,\ndespite how odd the ingredients are.
Perhaps one can only get this flavor while\neating in nature with friends.
Yer damn right on that count!
I love me some outdoor grub!
Uh, Cleo? Our soup isn't turning out\nlike yours at all. It's...very gross.
Can you maybe take a look and see\nwhat we did wrong?
Mind tasting ours and giving us\nsome pointers as well?
I made a few'a my own tweaks and it\nturned out aaaaall right! ...Er, right?
Yes yes, please hold on. I'll be certain\nto come around to all of you in turn.

But first, please excuse me for a moment.
Oh, but do give a shout if you need
something urgent or light another thing
on fire, yes?
I agree. Previously, she would always\nhang back from parties such as this.
But now she's right in the thick of things\nand having a great time. You think maybe\nall this outdoor cooking is the reason?
Yeah, I think so. I mean, I know she\nwanted to get better at this for us, but...
Well, I think it's helped her get\nCLOSER to all of us as well!
